Unit 7 — Game Development

Big Question

What makes a game worth playing?

Notice that this isn't asking how to program one.

Students already know that.

Now they're learning how to design one.

Section 7.1 — Understanding Games

Big Question

How do we describe games?

This comes almost directly from your Genres document.

7.1.1 What is a Game?

Not philosophically.

Practically.

Goals.

Rules.

Players.

Feedback.

Challenge.

7.1.2 Genres

Platformer.

RPG.

Simulation.

Strategy.

Students need this vocabulary.

7.1.3 Core Mechanics

I love your music analogy.

Genres are orchestras.

Mechanics are instruments.

This should absolutely stay.

